-- Malaysian Stock Movers: Ebworx, Favelle Favco, Gopeng, Smartag
-- B y   G a n   Y e n   K u a n
-- 2012-04-06T09:09:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/malaysian-stock-movers-ebworx-favelle-favco-gopeng-smartag.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Malaysia trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Kuala Lumpur.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index (FBMKLCI)  rose 0.3 percent to
1,598.87, snapping a two-day decline. The gauge climbed 0.2
percent this week.  Ebworx Bhd. (EBWX)  , a computer-software provider, rose
1.1 percent to 88.5 sen, a record close. Hitachi Ltd. plans to
make a buyout offer for its shares at 90 sen each, Ebworx said
in a statement.  OSK Ventures International Bhd. (OSKV)  , which
owns 25.4 percent of Ebworx, said it will accept the offer. OSK
Ventures gained 2.5 percent to 41.5 sen.  Favelle Favco Bhd. (FFB)  , a crane maker, advanced 2.9
percent to 1.41 ringgit, its steepest increase since March 14.
The company won orders totaling 102.1 million ringgit ($33
million), it said in a stock-exchange filing.  Gopeng Bhd. (GOP)  , an oil-palm planter, jumped 9.7
percent to 79 sen, its largest gain since Aug. 17, 2010. The
company proposed a final dividend of 9.8 sen per share, it said
in an exchange filing.  Smartag Solutions Bhd. (SMTG)  , a provider of radio-
frequency identification technology, climbed 2.3 percent to 22.5
sen, the most since March 28. The company won a government
contract to implement a mobile digital wallet system, it said in
a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
